data.title: Arnold Schwarzenegger's Fubar 2 goes into production
data.meta_description: The action comedy series will have eight one-hour episodes and touch upon family relationships, action, and comedy. A release date for Fubar S2 is yet to be announced. The show is created by Nick Santora, who is also executive producing  alongside Arnold.
data.text:
On Monday, Netflix announced that they have begun production for the second season of Arnold Schwarzenegger's Fubar. Previously, the makers announced that actor Carrie-Anne Moss has been added to the cast of the series' second season.

Netflix has unveiled a behind-the-sets video making an announcement that the production for the second season of Fubar is going to be big and of high value.

The returning cast of Fubar comprises Monica Barbaro, Fortune Feimster, Travis Van Winkle, Jay Baruchel, Aparna Brielle, Andy Buckley, Milan Carter, Fabiana Udenio and Barbara Eve Harris.

Fubar revolves around a CIA operative who is on the verge of retirement, discovers a family secret and is forced back into the field for one last job. The action comedy series will have eight episodes and touch upon family relationships, action, and comedy.
